
[1]numerous

   NU'MEROUS, a. [L.]

   1. Being many, or consisting of a great number of individuals; as a
   numerous army; a numerous body; a numerous people.

   2. Consisting of poetic numbers; melodious; musical. In prose, a style
   becomes numerous by the alternate disposition or intermixture of long
   and short syllables, or of long and short words; or by a judicious
   selection and disposition of smooth flowing words, and by closing the
   periods with important or well sounding words.
